Add citation panel at pyramid bottom-right + ship v0.1.0

For each year shown in the pyramid view, the bottom-right overlay
displays one of three citation forms:

1. Census years (1982 / 1990 / 2000 / 2010 / 2020):
   data source label + NBS census report URL.

2. Non-census historical years (1983-2024 excluding census):
   the CCM formulas plus the alignment step (PopulationAlignment),
   shown symbolically — no actual values substituted, per request.

3. Forecast years (after last NBS observed year 2024):
   the extrapolation function (LookupOrInterp last-value-constant
   over TotalBirths / SRB / TFR / MAFM / CrudeMarriageRate / e0),
   plus any counterfactual edits if the active scenario modified
   the inputs for the displayed year.

The citation Border is IsHitTestVisible=False so the pyramid's
400ms hover tooltip continues to work underneath it.

This marks the first usable version of the tool (v0.1.0).

